## B1Stack — ChurchApps Local Dev & K8s Orchestration

This repo orchestrates the ChurchApps B1 product suite. It does NOT contain application source code — the services live in `services/`, managed by git-aggregator via `repos.yaml`.

### Key Architecture
- `services/` — cloned service repos (gitignored, managed by `gitaggregate -c repos.yaml`)
- `docker/` — Dockerfiles for each service (volume-mount pattern for hot-reload)
- `mysql/init/` — SQL run by MySQL on first start (creates databases, not tables)
- `scripts/` — setup, init-db, health-check, reset-db, wait-ready
- `helm/b1stack/` — Helm umbrella chart (flat, no sub-charts; deployed on Hetzner b1-test)
- `Makefile` — DX shortcuts (`make up`, `make test`, `make health`, etc.)

### Services & Ports
| Service    | Port(s)   | Framework       |
|-----------|-----------|-----------------|
| mysql     | 3306      | MySQL 8.0       |
| api       | 8084/8087 | Node/tsx watch   |
| b1admin   | 3101      | React/Vite      |
| b1app     | 3301      | Next.js         |
| lessonsapi| 8090      | Node/nodemon (profile: full) |
| askapi    | 8097      | Node/nodemon (profile: full) |

### Connection Strings
- **Api**: Per-module env vars: `MEMBERSHIP_CONNECTION_STRING`, `ATTENDANCE_CONNECTION_STRING`, etc.
- **LessonsApi/AskApi**: Single `CONNECTION_STRING` env var
- **B1Admin env prefix**: `REACT_APP_*` (read at Vite start, restart required)
- **B1App env prefix**: `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`

### Rules
- Work in `services/` via feature branches — see CONTRIBUTING.md for git-aggregator workflow
- Use `make` targets instead of raw docker compose commands
- Named volumes prevent host node_modules from shadowing container's
- Hot-reload uses polling on macOS: `CHOKIDAR_USEPOLLING` / `WATCHPACK_POLLING`
- Helm chart uses `public.ecr.aws/bitnami/mysql` (not Docker Hub)
- Run `make init` after first `make up` to create DB tables
